.page
  %section
    %h2 Applications
    %p Welcome future student! We're glad that you've made the decision to start learning to program for the web. This program is designed to teach you the essentials quickly and give you the tools and support you need to keep learning and growing as a developer.
    %h3 Required Application Materials
    %ul
      %li Resume
      %li Cover Letter which addresses:
      %ul
        %li Your interest in programming
        %li Why you want to be a web developer
        %li Who you are as a person, particularly in the context of a team work-environment
      %li A "Hello World" app in Ruby on Rails committed to Github
    %h3 Optional Additional Materials: Creative Submissions
    %p This is a competetive application process. We strongly encourage all applicants to submit at least two of the three items below:
    %ul
      %li Any portfolio items that show us what you are working on; digital or analog projects are great
      %li Digital evidence of you being awesome. A video of you rapping, a poem about trees, or an animated gif of you doing interpretive dance. The idea is to give us a way to get to know you better as a person.
      %li Community engagement activity including attendance at Ruby Newbies, RailsGirls/RubyNest, the Portland Ruby Brigade, or activity on any related mailing lists or forums
    / <p>You can see some examples of excellent creative submissions <a hreff="*UNICORN SPARKLE* link to a page about submissions"> Here.</a></p>
    %p
      Please send all documents, stories, videos, and digital sculptures to
      %a{:href => "mailto:applications@portlandcodeschool.com"} applications@portlandcodeschool.com

